o and other early leaders of the Chinese Communist Party mobilized an influential labor movement at the beginning of their revolution, and whose history later became a touchstone of "political correctness" in the People's Republic of China. Once known as "China's Little Moscow," Anyuan came over time to symbolize a distinctively Chinese revolutionary tradition. Yet the meanings of that tradition remain highly contested, as contemporary Chinese debate their revolutionary past in search of a new political future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng, China : West)xPolitics and governmenty20th century. 0aCoal minerszChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aCommunismzChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aLabor movementzChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical culturezChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aRevolutionsxSocial aspectszChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial changezChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aWorking classzChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520954038423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520954038.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles